## Project context (READ FIRST)

Lumen is **not** the primary UI stack of this monorepo. It coexists with the
legacy stack and is currently used in a **very limited scope**:

- `apps/sample` still uses `@ledgerhq/react-ui` + `styled-components` for
  everything. Do **not** migrate other components to Lumen unless explicitly
  asked.
- The **only** Lumen usage today is the two device-selection buttons on the
  home page: `apps/sample/src/components/ConnectDevice/ConnectDeviceButtons.tsx`.
- `packages/devtools/**` is a separate package and does not use Lumen.

### How Lumen is wired in `apps/sample` (do not break this)

- **Tailwind v4** (`tailwindcss@^4`, `@tailwindcss/postcss`). Config in
  `apps/sample/tailwind.config.ts` uses `ledgerLivePreset` from
  `@ledgerhq/lumen-design-core`.
- `apps/sample/src/styles/lumen.css` deliberately **does NOT** `@import "tailwindcss";`
  (that would pull Tailwind preflight, a global reset that breaks react-ui).
  Instead it imports only the theme layer + **utilities UNLAYERED**.
  - Utilities must stay unlayered: react-ui ships an unlayered global reset
    (`button { color: inherit }`), and per the CSS cascade unlayered rules beat
    layered ones. Layered utilities would be overridden (white-on-white text).
- Dark mode: wrap Lumen components in an element with `className="dark"` (the app
  is dark-themed via react-ui). White primary button = `appearance="base"` (maps
  to `bg-interactive` = white in dark mode).
- Import the type-safe barrel: `import { Button } from "@ledgerhq/lumen-ui-react"`.

